text:
Coffee promotion price states 80 cents. When I ordered and wanted to pay stallholder said it's for small cup only, But not stated. Sheer misrepresentation.

Indian and Chinese economic rice are delicious though.

Ok S$5 lunch from Barchor Mee Stall, food presented was as shown and tasty, which is important as some places showing soft yolk hard white egg do not present it on actual. Teh Si Less Sugar at $1.40. A bit pricey for certain stalls and food, but affordable options exist. Most importantly, there are 3 Halal/Muslim-owned stalls (Nasi Padang, 24 hr AL DIA and Western) so Halal options are available - as Blk 451 Foodgle does not have any Halal stall since Burgs permanently closed. Also has a Le Le Lao Huo Tang stall, Economy Bee Hoon / Porridge (closed at this review), Economy Rice, Wanted T Plus Taiwan-Food, Bar Chor Noodles, Singapore Seafood Zichar and drinks stall.

Had dry fish ball noodle. 7 fish balls with the soup! 1st time encountered so many fish balls. Price was $5.50. Noodle oso quite a lot.  Asked for less chili but still lots of it.  Can't finish it. Should cut down to 4-5 nos fish ball, less noodle and sell for $5. Had diarrhea thereafter.  Not sure if due to this meal.ðŸ«¤

I pass My son $10 to order Prata $2.40 changed $7.60 and 2 drinks $1.80 each which is $3.60.
, the drinks stall so dishonest and only pass him back with coins of $2.00. By right is $4.00 $2 note and $1, 50c,2 of 20c, 10c. Beware of the dishonest act. End up I told her other drink stall colleague then she return back the $2.00
